#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:2
msgid "Compression"
msgstr "压缩"

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:4
msgid ""
"Compression can greatly decrease the size of the response body and hence "
"increase the speed of a web app. Use the `compression "
"<https://github.com/expressjs/compression>`__ middleware to enable gzip "
"compression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:10
msgid "Installation"
msgstr "Installation"

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:12
msgid "Firstly, install the required package:"
msgstr "Firstly, install the required package:"

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:18
msgid "Once the installation is completed, apply it as a global middleware."
msgstr "Once the installation is completed, apply it as a global middleware."

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:28
msgid ""
"info **Hint** If you work with ``FastifyAdapter``, consider using "
"`fastify-compress <https://github.com/fastify/fastify-compress>`__ "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/compression.rst:32
msgid ""
"For a **high-traffic** website in production, the best way to put "
"compression in place is to implement it at a reverse proxy level. In that"
" case, you do not need to use compression middleware."
msgstr ""

